This is the repository root. It's an opinionated agentic coding system with three layers: a strict Rust lint regime the workspace itself is built under, a context-delivery/generation toolchain (`ctx-access`, `ctx-summarize`, `ctx-verify`, plus siblings `ctx-context`/`ctx-scan`/`ctx-check`/`ctx-cage`), and a deferred architecture-audit layer. Depending on the root gets you the whole system: a `crates/` workspace of independently-testable binaries, the prompt/agent pipeline that drives `.ctx` generation, the config files pinning exactly how that workspace is built and linted, and `docs/` as the authoritative record of current state versus retired designs.

The load-bearing coupling runs through config, not code: `Cargo.toml`'s workspace lint table must stay byte-identical to `template/Cargo.toml`'s (the "dogfood" guarantee — this repo builds under the same regime it hands to generated projects), `clippy.toml`'s hard-fail thresholds pair with soft tiers enforced only by `scripts/rationale_check.py` and an undocumented dylint crate, and `rust-toolchain.toml` gates which `rustfmt.toml` options are actually honored. `scripts/` enforces these policies as CI gates using a shared git-ls-files enumeration convention and a `FAIL: path:line` output format that `ctx-verify` parses. `agents/` and `prompts/` together form the summarization pipeline's non-Rust half — prompts are plain files loaded verbatim, agents are pure stdin/stdout transports, and the `intent_divergence:` label is shared vocabulary between `summarizer-rollup.md` and `auditor.md` that must not drift. `docs/` is where rationale and current-vs-retired status live; `sandbox/` is fully retired in favor of `crates/ctx-cage`.

Cross-cutting invariants: no `unsafe`, no `#[allow]` anywhere, typed errors only, secrets never read by a model or committed, and every crate/test fakes its environment/subprocess boundary rather than touching real disk or shelling out. `README.md` documents a quickstart workflow (`ctx-access init-task/end-task`, `.context/` tree) that is explicitly not yet implemented.

The subtree matches its stated intent — Layer 1 is enforced and dogfooded, Layer 2 crates exist per the architecture, Layer 3 is deferred as declared.